# Binance Testnet API credentials (HMAC-SHA256)
# Create them at https://testnet.binance.vision/
# Permissions needed: read account + spot trading.
# As of PR B, `npm run decide` PLACES REAL ORDERS on the testnet (fake money, but
# a real exchange round-trip) — the spot-trading permission is now actually used.
# NEVER commit the real .env file.
BINANCE_TESTNET_API_KEY=your_testnet_api_key_here
BINANCE_TESTNET_API_SECRET=your_testnet_api_secret_here

# Supabase (OPTIONAL — server-side persistence for the ATH/ATL cache)
# Leave BOTH commented out to run without the cache: the bot still works and
# computes ATH/ATL from the long series each run (a single warning is logged).
# Uncomment and fill them in to enable the cache.
#
# Use the SERVICE ROLE key: this is a backend, the key bypasses RLS and must
# stay server-side only. NEVER expose it client-side, NEVER commit it.
# Find both in the Supabase dashboard → Project Settings → API.
#SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-ref.supabase.co
#SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your_service_role_key_here

# Anthropic API (decision layer — required for `npm run decide`)
# Get a key at https://console.anthropic.com. The decision layer calls Claude
# directly; without ANTHROPIC_API_KEY, `npm run decide` exits with a clear error.
# ANTHROPIC_MODEL is optional — defaults to claude-haiku-4-5 (cheap, for
# validating the plumbing). Switch to claude-sonnet-4-6 for real decision quality.
#ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-your_key_here
#ANTHROPIC_MODEL=claude-haiku-4-5

# Optional: commit SHA stamped on each decision for traceability. CI usually
# sets this; locally the code falls back to `git rev-parse`, then null.
#GIT_SHA=

# Execution layer (OPTIONAL — the economic brain has sane defaults in config).
# The bot manages its OWN virtual portfolio valued at real prices, seeded with
# this sovereign capital — independent of the inflated, monthly-reset testnet
# balances. Leave commented out to use the config defaults.
#  - STARTING_CAPITAL_USD: virtual starting capital in USD (default 500)
#  - FEE_PERCENT: modeled fee per movement, in percent of notional (default 0.1)
# (Allocation caps — 35% big / 15% small / 30% min cash — live in config, not env.)
#STARTING_CAPITAL_USD=500
#FEE_PERCENT=0.1

# Alerting (OPTIONAL — the scheduler's emergency safety net). All best-effort: if
# any of these is unset or unreachable, the bot logs and keeps beating — it never
# fails a heartbeat over an alerting outage. Set them in the real .env locally, then
# carry them to Railway env vars at deploy. The alert THRESHOLDS (floor streak 10,
# consecutive failures 3) live in config, not here.
#
#  - Telegram bot for INTERNAL alerts (sent from the code). Create a bot via
#    @BotFather to get the token; get your chat id by messaging the bot then reading
#    https://api.telegram.org/bot<token>/getUpdates. Prove it end-to-end with
#    `npm run notify:test`.
#TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=123456789:your_bot_token_here
#TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID=your_chat_id_here
#
#  - Healthchecks.io dead-man's-switch. The bot pings this URL at the end of every
#    clean beat; Healthchecks emails YOU if the pings stop (process down / cron
#    broken / crash). Configure period 5 min + grace 15–20 min in their dashboard.
#    Create a check at https://healthchecks.io and paste its ping URL here.
#HEALTHCHECKS_PING_URL=https://hc-ping.com/your-uuid-here
